main event: A bright white light was sighted over Silver Bay, Minnesota on November 21, 1960 that disappeared over the western horizon after about 20 minutes.
interesting points: The object was described as circular in shape and 4 times the size of a star.
The object was a bright white light that did not exhibit any other features.
The object was sighted by the superintendent of a machine shop, who was considered a reliable observer.
Several similar sightings had been reported in the Duluth, Minnesota area recently, suggesting a common pattern.
The Air Force analyst suggested the object was likely the planet Venus setting in the west.
